The major focus of the MIDAS research partnership has been pandemic influenza. In response to the MIDAS mission (see http://grants.nih.gov/grants/guide/notice-files/NOT-GM-06–106.html), a number of large ABMs describing influenza transmission were developed. The main purpose of the models was to examine possible intervention strategies that would protect the general public from morbidity and mortality should an influenza pandemic strike. One of the initial objectives in all disease transmission studies is to determine the basic R0 value. The goal of intervention is to reduce R0 below the self-sustaining threshold of R0\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
